The paper discusses a problem in software engineering related to certifying that system requirements are correctly implemented by source code. This suggests that the paper belongs to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) category. The paper also mentions Business Process Modeling, which is related to Computer Engineering (cs.CE) and Database (cs.DB) categories. The paper proposes a new method for connecting business process models to source code, which involves specifying behavior using a business language, suggesting that the paper may also belong to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) category. Finally, the paper mentions the use of automated tests, which is related to Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) category.
